{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869370822,"sessionID":"ses_285f010e7ffeC5lGqOCzuKY0u1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a101e31001Go38EUO6WXaPrN","messageID":"msg_d7a100c27001MDdWO0sQ2339QQ","sessionID":"ses_285f010e7ffeC5lGqOCzuKY0u1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9fe9f7c1be06402785a77939","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n11: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n12: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n13: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n14: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n15: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n16: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n17: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n18: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n19: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n20: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n21: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n22: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n23: \n24: ## Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n25: \n26: ```python\n27: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n28: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n29: \n30: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n31: ```\n32: \n33: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n34: \n35: ```python\n36: __all__ = [\n37:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n38:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n39:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n40: ]\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ## Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n44: \n45: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n46: \n47: | Component | Resolved settings |\n48: |-----------|-------------------|\n49: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n50: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n51: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n52: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n53: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n54: \n55: ## `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n59:     def __init__(\n60:         self,\n61:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n62:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n63:         ttl: int = 3600,\n64:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n65:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n66:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n67:         verbose: bool = False,\n68:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n69:     ): ...\n70: \n71:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n72: \n73:     def __enter__(self): ...\n74:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n75: \n76:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n77: \n78:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n79:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n80:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n81:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n82:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n83:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n84: ```\n85: \n86: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n87: \n88: ## `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n89: \n90: ```python\n91: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n92:     def __init__(\n93:         self,\n94:         agent_name: str,\n95:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n96:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n97:         verbose: bool = False,\n98:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n99:         timeout: int = 120,\n100:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n101:     ): ...\n102: \n103:     def __enter__(self): ...\n104:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n105: \n106:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n107: \n108:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n109: ```\n110: \n111: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n112: \n113: ## `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n114: \n115: ```python\n116: class ControlPlaneClient:\n117:     def __init__(\n118:         self,\n119:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n120:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n121:         timeout: int = 120,\n122:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n123:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n124:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n125:     ): ...\n126: \n127:     def create_session(\n128:         self,\n129:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n130:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n131:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n132:         ttl: int = 3600,\n133:     ) -> str: ...\n134: \n135:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n136: \n137:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n138: ```\n139: \n140: ### Control plane — HTTP\n141: \n142: | Method | Path | Notes |\n143: |--------|------|-------|\n144: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n145: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n146: \n147: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n148: \n149: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n150: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n151: \n152: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n153: \n154: ## `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n155: \n156: ```python\n157: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n158:     def __init__(\n159:         self,\n160:         session_id: str,\n161:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n162:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n163:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n164:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n165:         timeout: int = 120,\n166:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n167:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n168:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n169:     ): ...\n170: \n171:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n172: \n173:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n174:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n175:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n176:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n177:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n178:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n179:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Data plane (Code Interpreter) — base URL\n183: \n184: If `base_url` is not provided:\n185: \n186: ```text\n187: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n188: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Data plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n192: \n193: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n194: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n195: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n196: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n197: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n198: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n199: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n200: \n201: **Headers:**\n202: \n203: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n204: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n205: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n206: \n207: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n208: \n209: ## `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n213:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n214: \n215:     def __init__(\n216:         self,\n217:         router_url: str,\n218:         namespace: str,\n219:         agent_name: str,\n220:         timeout: int = 120,\n221:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n222:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n223:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n224:     ): ...\n225: \n226:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n227: \n228:     def invoke(\n229:         self,\n230:         session_id: str,\n231:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n232:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n233:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n234: \n235:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Data plane (Agent Runtime) — base URL\n239: \n240: ```text\n241: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n242: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n243: ```\n244: \n245: ### Data plane — HTTP\n246: \n247: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n248: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n249: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n250: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n251: \n252: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n253: \n254: ## `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: def create_session(\n258:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n259:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n260: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n261: ```\n262: \n263: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n264: \n265: ## `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n266: \n267: ```python\n268: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n272: \n273: ## `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n274: \n275: ```python\n276: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ## Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n280: \n281: ```python\n282: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n283:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n284:     pass\n285: \n286: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n287:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n288:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n289:         self.stderr = stderr\n290:         self.command = command\n291:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n292: \n293: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n294:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n295:     pass\n296: \n297: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n298:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n299:     pass\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n303: \n304: ```toml\n305: dependencies = [\n306:     \"requests\",\n307:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n308:     \"cryptography\",\n309: ]\n310: ```\n311: \n312: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n313: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n314: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n319: \n320: ## Purpose\n321: \n322: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n323: \n324: ## Requirements\n325: \n326: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n327: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n330: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n331: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n332: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n335: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n336: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n337: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n340: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n341: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n342: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n343: \n344: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n345: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n348: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n349: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n350: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n351: \n352: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n353: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n354: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n355: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n356: \n357: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n358: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n359: \n360: #### Scenario: Context manager\n361: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n362: - **WHEN** the block exits\n363: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n366: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n367: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n368: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n369: \n370: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n371: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n372: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n373: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n374: \n375: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n376: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Create session\n379: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n380: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n381: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: Delete session\n384: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n385: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n386: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n387: \n388: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n389: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n390: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n391: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n392: \n393: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n394: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: Execute command\n397: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n398: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n399: \n400: #### Scenario: Files API\n401: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n403: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n404: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n405: \n406: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n407: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n410: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n411: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n412: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n413: \n414: ### Requirement: Session header management\n415: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n418: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n419: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n420: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n421: \n422: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n423: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Command failure\n426: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n427: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n428: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n431: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n432: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n433: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n434: \n435: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n436: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n439: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n440: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n441: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n444: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n445: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n446: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n447: \n448: ---\n449: \n450: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n451: \n452: ---\n453: \n454: Previous proposal:\n455: [Stage ST-1 completed]\n456: \n457: Include: architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy.\n\n(End of file - total 457 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Package layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775869370805,"end":1775869370819}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869370834,"sessionID":"ses_285f010e7ffeC5lGqOCzuKY0u1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1019df001z9vu1SEwU67LiU","messageID":"msg_d7a100c27001MDdWO0sQ2339QQ","sessionID":"ses_285f010e7ffeC5lGqOCzuKY0u1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5e85887f4e6440c78a88a5f5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** sdk-python  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-1 (Draft)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (T001-T010)\n13: \n14: - [ ] **T001** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class with constructor\n15:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n16:   - *Verify:* Accepts `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`, `base_url`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n17:   - *Test:* Instantiate client, verify default values\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T002** Implement base URL construction from router components\n20:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n21:   - *Verify:* When `base_url` not provided, constructs `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n22:   - *Test:* Verify correct URL format\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T003** Implement `_request()` helper with session header\n25:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n26:   - *Verify:* Adds `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` header to all requests\n27:   - *Test:* Make request, verify header present\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T004** Implement `execute_tool(tool_name, parameters, timeout)` via data plane\n30:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n31:   - *Verify:* POSTs to `api/execute` with JSON body containing tool_name, parameters, timeout\n32:   - *Test:* Execute tool, verify request format\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T005** Implement `list_tools()` via data plane\n35:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n36:   - *Verify:* GET `api/tools`, returns list of available tools\n37:   - *Test:* List tools, verify response parsing\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T006** Implement `get_tool_schema(tool_name)` via data plane\n40:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n41:   - *Verify:* GET `api/tools/{tool_name}/schema`, returns tool schema\n42:   - *Test:* Get schema, verify response\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T007** Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` via data plane\n45:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n46:   - *Verify:* POST multipart form data to `api/files` with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n47:   - *Test:* Upload file, verify multipart request\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T008** Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` via data plane\n50:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n51:   - *Verify:* GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`, writes to local path\n52:   - *Test:* Download file, verify stream handling\n53: \n54: - [ ] **T009** Implement `list_files(path=\".\")` via data plane\n55:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n56:   - *Verify:* GET `api/files` with query parameter `path`\n57:   - *Test:* List files, verify query param\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T010** Implement `close()` method\n60:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n61:   - *Verify:* Closes HTTP session\n62:   - *Test:* Verify session is closed\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient (T011-T020)\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T011** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class with constructor\n69:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n70:   - *Verify:* Accepts `name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose=False`, `session_id=None`\n71:   - *Test:* Instantiate client, verify defaults\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T012** Implement router URL validation\n74:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n75:   - *Verify:* Raises `ValueError` if neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` env var is set\n76:   - *Test:* Instantiate without router_url, verify ValueError raised\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T013** Implement `_init_data_plane()` and session creation\n79:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n80:   - *Verify:* If no `session_id` provided, calls `cp_client.create_session()`, then initializes data plane client\n81:   - *Test:* Instantiate without session_id, verify create_session called\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T014** Implement data plane init failure handling\n84:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n85:   - *Verify:* If `_init_data_plane()` fails after session created, logs warning, deletes session, sets session_id to None, re-raises\n86:   - *Test:* Simulate failure, verify cleanup\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T015** Implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n89:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n90:   - *Verify:* `__exit__` calls `stop()`, which closes data plane and deletes control plane session if it was created by this client\n91:   - *Test:* Use client as context manager, verify cleanup on exit\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T016** Implement `execute_tool(tool_name, parameters, timeout)`\n94:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n95:   - *Verify:* Delegates to data plane client, returns execution result\n96:   - *Test:* Execute tool, verify result\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T017** Implement `list_tools()` and `get_tool_schema(tool_name)`\n99:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n100:   - *Verify:* Delegate to data plane client methods\n101:   - *Test:* List tools and get schema\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T018** Implement file operations (`upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`)\n104:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n105:   - *Verify:* Delegate to data plane client methods\n106:   - *Test:* Each operation works correctly\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T019** Implement `stop()` method\n109:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n110:   - *Verify:* Closes data plane session, deletes control plane session if created by this client\n111:   - *Test:* Call stop, verify cleanup\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T020** Update `agentcube/__init__.py` with AgentRuntimeClient exports\n114:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n115:   - *Verify:* `AgentRuntimeClient` is properly exported\n116:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ### Phase 3: Tests & Examples (T021-T024)\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T021** Write unit tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n123:   - *File:* `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n124:   - *Verify:* All operations make correct HTTP requests\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T022** Write unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient\n127:   - *File:* `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n128:   - *Verify:* Full lifecycle, context manager, error handling\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T023** Create example usage script for AgentRuntimeClient\n131:   - *File:* `sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_example.py`\n132:   - *Verify:* Demonstrates AgentRuntimeClient usage\n133: \n134: - [ ] **T024** Verify full package exports\n135:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`, `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n136:   - *Verify:* All clients properly exported\n137:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient; from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## Dependencies\n142: \n143: | Task | Depends On |\n144: |------|------------|\n145: | T002 | T001 |\n146: | T003 | T001 |\n147: | T004 | T002, T003 |\n148: | T005 | T002, T003 |\n149: | T006 | T002, T003 |\n150: | T007 | T002, T003 |\n151: | T008 | T002, T003 |\n152: | T009 | T002, T003 |\n153: | T010 | T001 |\n154: | T011 | AR-027 T001-T003 |\n155: | T012 | T011 |\n156: | T013 | T001, T011 |\n157: | T014 | T013 |\n158: | T015 | T013, T019 |\n159: | T016 | T013 |\n160: | T017 | T013 |\n161: | T018 | T013 |\n162: | T019 | T010, (AR-027 T007) |\n163: | T020 | T011 |\n164: | T021 | T001-T010 |\n165: | T022 | T011-T019 |\n166: | T023 | T011-T019 |\n167: | T024 | T020 |\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Verification Checklist\n172: \n173: - [ ] AC001: AgentRuntimeClient constructs with proper defaults (name, namespace, ttl, verbose)\n174: - [ ] AC002: AgentRuntimeClient creates session via ControlPlaneClient when session_id not provided\n175: - [ ] AC003: AgentRuntimeClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n176: - [ ] AC004: AgentRuntimeClient handles data plane init failure with session cleanup\n177: - [ ] AC005: AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n178: - [ ] AC006: execute_tool sends correct request to data plane\n179: - [ ] AC007: list_tools returns available tools from data plane\n180: - [ ] AC008: get_tool_schema returns schema for specified tool\n181: - [ ] AC009: upload_file uploads files via multipart to data plane\n182: - [ ] AC010: download_file downloads files as streams to local path\n183: - [ ] AC011: list_files returns file listing from data plane\n184: - [ ] AC012: stop closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n185: - [ ] AC013: Session header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all data plane requests\n186: - [ ] AC014: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## References\n191: \n192: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n193: - Stub Implementation: `changes/AR-027` (Phase 6: AgentRuntimeClient Stub)\n194: - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n195: - Control Plane API: `workload-manager/api.md`\n\n(End of file - total 195 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-1 (Draft)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (T001-T010)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class with constructor\n  - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* Accepts `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`, `base_url`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n  - *Test:* Instantiate client, verify default values\n\n- [ ] **T002** Implement base URL construction from router components\n  - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775869370802,"end":1775869370832}}}}
