{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869452280,"sessionID":"ses_285f010e7ffeC5lGqOCzuKY0u1","part":{"id":"prt_d7a10e0480016igGh9iQjxCXpa","messageID":"msg_d7a10c15c001tJxnABPT9xOKPd","sessionID":"ses_285f010e7ffeC5lGqOCzuKY0u1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_63ae1b3543214c27933be18b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (T001-T008)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* File created with class `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n  - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n- [ ] **T002** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` constructor\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* Accepts `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n  - *Test:* Instantiate client, verify default values\n\n- [ ] **T003** Implement base URL construction from router components\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* When no explicit base_url, constructs `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n  - *Test:* Verify correct URL format with various inputs\n\n- [ ] **T004** Add SESSION_HEADER class constant\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n  - *Test:* Assert class constant equals expected value\n\n- [ ] **T005** Implement `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` method\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* POSTs JSON payload to base URL with session header\n  - *Test:* Mock HTTP, verify POST request format and headers\n\n- [ ] **T006** Implement `close()` method\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* Closes HTTP session\n  - *Test:* Call close, verify session closed\n\n- [ ] **T007** Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n  - *Verify:* Exports `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n  - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n- [ ] **T008** Add unit tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n  - *File:* `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* Constructor, URL construction, invoke, close methods tested\n  - *Test:* pytest runs successfully\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient (T009-T019)\n\n- [ ] **T009** Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* File created with class `AgentRuntimeClient`\n  - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n\n- [ ] **T010** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` with router URL validation\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* Accepts `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`; validates router_url from arg or ROUTER_URL env var\n  - *Test:* Instantiate with valid router_url; test ValueError when missing\n\n- [ ] **T011** Implement session bootstrap via GET request\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* When session_id not provided, GET invocation URL and extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - *Test:* Mock GET response with session header; test ValueError when header missing\n\n- [ ] **T012** Implement reuse of provided session_id (skip bootstrap)\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* When session_id provided, use it directly without bootstrap\n  - *Test:* Instantiate with session_id, verify no bootstrap GET made\n\n- [ ] **T013** Initialize AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* Creates AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient instance with correct params\n  - *Test:* Verify dp_client is set after init\n\n- [ ] **T014** Implement context manager `__enter__` and `__exit__`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* `__enter__` returns self, `__exit__` calls `close()`\n  - *Test:* Use client in `with` block, verify close called on exit\n\n- [ ] **T015** Implement `invoke(payload, timeout)` method\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* Delegates to dp_client.invoke, raises ValueError if session_id not initialized\n  - *Test:* Call invoke with valid session; call with None session_id\n\n- [ ] **T016** Implement default timeout handling in invoke\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* When timeout=None, uses (connect_timeout, self.timeout) tuple\n  - *Test:* Mock request, verify timeout tuple\n\n- [ ] **T017** Implement custom timeout in invoke\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* When timeout is provided, uses provided value\n  - *Test:* Invoke with timeout=60, verify timeout passed correctly\n\n- [ ] **T018** Implement `close()` method\n  - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n  - *Verify:* Closes data plane client and HTTP session\n  - *Test:* Call close, verify resources cleaned up\n\n- [ ] **T019** Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to import from agent_runtime.py\n  - *File:* `agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - *Verify:* `from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient` in __all__\n  - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Integration Tests & Examples (T020-T023)\n\n- [ ] **T020** Write unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n  - *File:* `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n  - *Verify:* Constructor, context manager, bootstrap, invoke tested\n  - *Test:* pytest runs successfully\n\n- [ ] **T021** Create example usage script\n  - *File:* `examples/agent_runtime_example.py`\n  - *Verify:* Demonstrates AgentRuntimeClient usage patterns\n  - *Test:* Script runs without syntax errors\n\n- [ ] **T022** Run full package import test\n  - *Verify:* All exports work correctly\n  - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient; from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n- [ ] **T023** Run linter/typecheck on new code\n  - *Verify:* No linting errors\n  - *Test:* ruff/ruff check and mypy pass\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Task | Depends On |\n|------|------------|\n| T002 | T001 |\n| T003 | T002 |\n| T004 | T001 |\n| T005 | T003, T004 |\n| T006 | T001 |\n| T007 | T001, T005 |\n| T008 | T001-T007 |\n| T010 | T009 |\n| T011 | T010, (T001-T007 for dp_client) |\n| T012 | T010 |\n| T013 | T011 |\n| T014 | T013, T018 |\n| T015 | T013 |\n| T016 | T015 |\n| T017 | T015 |\n| T018 | T013 |\n| T019 | T009, T010 |\n| T020 | T009-T019 |\n| T021 | T009-T019 |\n| T022 | T007, T019 |\n| T023 | T001-T022 |\n\n---\n\n## Verification Checklist\n\n- [ ] AC001: AgentRuntimeClient constructs with proper defaults (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout)\n- [ ] AC002: AgentRuntimeClient creates session via GET when session_id not provided\n- [ ] AC003: AgentRuntimeClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n- [ ] AC004: AgentRuntimeClient handles missing session header during bootstrap with ValueError\n- [ ] AC005: AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n- [ ] AC006: invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy\n- [ ] AC007: invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload\n- [ ] AC008: invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header\n- [ ] AC009: invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None\n- [ ] AC010: invoke() uses custom timeout when provided\n- [ ] AC011: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n- [ ] AC012: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant\n- [ ] AC013: close() closes the requests.Session\n- [ ] AC014: Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n- Design: `python-sdk/design.md` (AgentRuntimeClient sections)\n- Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Related: AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient implementation)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [117:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [120:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [127:59] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/__init__.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":116,"character":27},"end":{"line":116,"character":42}},"message":"Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"","severity":1,"code":"reportArgumentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription"